race.comment: KILMISTER (9) brings the best last start performance into this, racing away with a dominant BM52 win at Wodonga to score by four lengths. This is slightly harder but not by a lot, and if he's able to hold that form he should go close again. BOULDER JACK (2) was poor over 1400m last time at Echuca in a stronger race. His run prior when second at Bendigo reads well for this and if he gets across he'll go close. FREDERICK (5) was disappointing second up at Yarra Valley but had been good fresh at Moe. Third up now, he draws to effect for Riordan and he should bounce back to form. JUDGE KELLIE (11) presents third up off a solid run at Hamilton last time out. With early luck she should run a strong race. DANDINO BELLE (16) hasn't won in a long time but did enough fresh and could place again.
